&#39;, b&#39;&#39;).upper() + b&#39;!&#39;; print(x) r.sendline(x) print(&#34;

&#34;+ r.recvline()[34:].decode() + &#34;

&#34;) r.recvline() discards the server&rsquo;s greeting. The second recvline() receives the word. Stripping 
, uppercasing, prepending ? and appending ! builds the protocol-correct response in one expression. r.recvline()[34:] skips the fixed preamble text and prints the flag.
What I Learned Custom-protocol challenges often require nothing more than reading the spec carefully and implementing the formatting rule. Pwntools remote with recvline / sendline is the fastest way to prototype a protocol client — the only real work is understanding what format the server expects back.
